**Simple Joke Website**

Below is an example of a simple website written in HTML that displays a random joke when you click the "Tell Me a Joke" button.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Joke Website</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        }

        #jokes-container {
            width: 50%;
            margin: 40px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        button {
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            color: white;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }

        button:hover {
            background-color: #3e8e41;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="jokes-container">
        <h2>Joke Website</h2>
        <p id="joke"></p>
        <button onclick="tellMeAJoke()">Tell Me a Joke</button>
    </div>

    <script>
        // List of jokes
        const jokes = [
            { joke: "Why don't scientists trust atoms? Because they make up everything.", punchline: "Why don't scientists trust atoms?" },
            { joke: "What do you call a fake noodle? An impasta!", punchline: "What do you call a fake noodle?" },
            { joke: "Why did the scarecrow win an award? Because he was outstanding in his field.", punchline: "Why did the scarecrow win an award?" },
            { joke: "Why don't eggs tell jokes? They'd crack each other up!", punchline: "Why don't eggs tell jokes?" }
        ];

        // Function to display a random joke
        function tellMeAJoke() {
            const randomIndex = Math.floor(Math.random() * jokes.length);
            const selectedJoke = jokes[randomIndex];
            document.getElementById("joke").innerHTML = `Here's one: ${selectedJoke.joke}<br>Why? Because ${selectedJoke.punchline}`;
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

**How it works**

1. We define a list of jokes in the JavaScript code.
2. When you click the "Tell Me a Joke" button, the `tellMeAJoke()` function is called.
3. The `tellMeAJoke()` function generates a random index for the joke list and selects a joke from it.
4. It then displays the selected joke on the webpage.

**Example Use Case**

You can save this code in an HTML file (e.g., `jokes.html`) and open it in your web browser to see the website in action. Clicking the "Tell Me a Joke" button will display a random joke from the list.

